  // MOB SPAWN EGGS:
  // Spawn eggs (e.g., creeper_spawn_egg, zombie_spawn_egg) render the actual entity/mob on the pillar
  // When you place a spawn egg on a pillar, the mob will face the direction you were looking
  // The mob is displayed on top of the pillar and will spawn particles like other items
  // 
  // MAKING MOBS SPIN:
  // To make a mob spin continuously, rename the spawn egg to "spin" using an anvil
  // The name must be exactly "spin" (case-insensitive, so "Spin" or "SPIN" also works)
  // Mobs with "spin" name tag will rotate continuously (40% slower than regular items)
  // Mobs without "spin" name tag will stay facing the direction you were looking when placed
  // 
  // ROTATING MOBS:
  // You can rotate mobs by Shift+Right-Clicking the pillar (rotates 180 degrees each time)
  // This works for both spinning and non-spinning mobs
